<p>Update</p>



<p>COVID-19 School Closure</p>



<p><strong>April 14, 2020</strong></p>



<p>Governor Tate Reeves announced that all public schools in Mississippi will remain closed for the remainder of this semester, due to the continued concerns about COVID-19 (Coronavirus).  He stressed that although our schools will be closed, instruction will continue through distance learning strategies.  You will be hearing more about this from your child’s school.  <br></p>



<p>During this time of school closures, Hancock County School District will continue to offer Grab-n-Go meals to children ages 18 and under.  Meals may be picked up at South Hancock Elementary and Hancock North Central Elementary, between 11:00am-12:00pm.  Meals are distributed by drive thru Grab-n-Go, as vehicles proceed through the bus lanes.  <br></p>



<p>We will continue to be in communication with you in the coming days as we all work together to get through this crisis.  We appreciate your continued support and hope you and your family stay healthy and safe.  <br></p>



